# Wedding site — core rules

The single source of truth for product and stack is **ARCHITECTURE.md** at the repo root. For larger changes, align with it and **§18 “Rule for everything new”**.

## Order for adding features (summary)

1. Data and config → `src/entities/<slice>/` (optional thin re-export in `lib/config/*.ts`); see **ARCHITECTURE.md** §3.3.
2. UI strings → **both** `messages/ru.json` and `messages/en.json` **in the same change**.
3. New page section → `src/widgets/<name>/`, wire in `app/[locale]/page.tsx`, register in `@entities/site-nav` (or `lib/config/nav.ts` re-export).
4. New UI primitive → `src/shared/ui/` only (`components/` is deprecated). Design-system classes only (Tailwind tokens / theme variables), no inline colors.

## Do not hardcode

- Colors: no `style={{ color: '#...' }}` or magic hex in JSX for styling.
- User-facing copy: no raw strings in components — use `next-intl` keys.
- Data lists: no `const items = [{ title: '...' }]` in UI — move to config.

## Diffs

Change only what the task requires. Avoid drive-by refactors and unrelated files.

## Humans and AI

The same expectations for the team live in **docs/CODING_STANDARDS.md** (mirror of these rules).
